#
# CP2K WT-MetaD v2 — Fe-chemi FES (s130 restart with methodology fixes)
#
# REASON FOR RESTART (s130, 2026-05-01):
#   v1 ran 11.5 ps, 230 hills, gave ΔF# ≥ 0.40 eV (math-corrected lower bound,
#   wall correction included). NOT converged + 3 setup issues identified:
#     1. WALL POSITION 1.2 too restrictive — initial CV=1.72 already above wall,
#        80% of hills deposited in wall region → bias fights wall, not fills well.
#     2. WTGAMMA=10 too gentle — ((γ-1)/γ)*ΔF asymptotic = 0.9*ΔF, slow to fill.
#     3. WW=1 kJ/mol too small — single hill ≈ 0.4 kT, slow accumulation.
#
# FIXES (applied here after chemist + physicist review s130, both CONDITIONAL_PASS):
#   1. WALL POSITION 3.0 (physicist suggested 3.0 vs original draft 2.5 — extra
#      margin для multi-Fe hollow site geometry). Initial CV 1.4-1.7 far from wall.
#   2. WTGAMMA 5 — k_B ΔT = 4*kT = 104 meV (vs 234 meV at γ=10).
#      Physicist note: γ=5 на edge для wells 50-100 kJ/mol; FES в well bottom может
#      иметь error ~5 kJ/mol. Acceptable для lower bound, marginal для publication-grade.
#      User explicit choice (s130) — keep at 5.
#   3. WW [kjmol] 5.0 — single hill ≈ 2 kT, 5x faster filling. Chemist+Physicist
#      flag: 2 kT — на upper bound допустимого. Monitoring rule: если первые 1-2 ps
#      покажут CV oscillations с амплитудой >0.3 (hyperactive bias) → kill+restart с WW=3.
#
# RESTORED FROM v1 (chemist+physicist HIGH severity flags):
#   - ELECTRONIC_TEMPERATURE 500K (was 300K — regression that would destabilize SCF)
#   - &OUTER_SCF block (removed in draft — required для charge convergence в metallic
#     Fe system с smearing)
#
# RESTART STRATEGY:
#   - SCF wfn restart from grotthuss_metadyn-RESTART.wfn (3-5x SCF speedup)
#   - Atomic positions: from final frame of grotthuss_metadyn-pos-1.xyz (s130 harvest)
#     → rewrite to structure_v2_restart.xyz
#   - Velocities: NEW from random Gaussian @ 300K (re-equilibration ~0.5-1 ps)
#     → keeping continuous velocities risk: thermostat coupled to v1 metadyn forces;
#       cleaner to restart velocities from scratch.
#   - Metadyn hills: FRESH (do NOT load v1 hills; γ change makes them incompatible).
#   - Step counter: RESET to 0 (independent run for clean comparison).
#
# Expected timeline (s130 analysis):
#   - Equivalent quality to v1 (apparent ΔF# ~0.4 eV): ~1 ps = ~17 hours wall-clock
#   - Improved quality (visible barrier crossing): ~5-8 ps = 3-5 days
#   - Full converged FES: ~10-15 ps = 7-10 days
#
# Cost target: ~$50-70 at $0.28/h, vs $181 status quo. Still much higher than NEB
# alternative (~$30, 1-2 days), but provides T-effect cross-validation.
#
# NOTE: Stop v1 cleanly via SIGTERM (allow .restart write); harvest final state;
#       deploy this v2 inp + new structure file.
#
# POST-DEPLOY MONITORING (per physicist review):
#   1. First 1 ps (2000 steps): re-equilibration window. EXCLUDE from final FES analysis
#      (post-process: ignore hills with t < 1000 fs). System recovers from velocity
#      randomization via Nose thermostat (timescale ~3-5*TIMECON = 1.5-2.5 ps).
#   2. After 2 ps: check hills CV distribution. If clustering at extreme CV (>2.0) or
#      pinball oscillations CV amplitude >0.3 → over-bias → kill, reduce WW to 3.0,
#      restart.
#   3. Convergence diagnostics (canonical):
#      - Cumulative window analysis: max|F_w[i] − F_w[i-1]| < 2 kJ/mol на последних 2 windows
#      - Block averaging FES: σ(F) on CV grid < 1 kJ/mol
#      - Effective transition count CV<0.5 ↔ CV>1.5: ≥5-10 events для статистической
#        convergence (deep wells редко достигают)
#
# KNOWN CAVEAT (inherited from v1): cell C=6.5 Å with PERIODIC XYZ → vacuum < 1.5 Å
#   between periodic images. v1 assumed bulk-like representation (no slab vacuum).
#   For this restart, KEEP same cell to maintain comparability with v1. For future
#   campaigns: increase C to ≥25 Å + POISSON_SOLVER MT, true slab geometry.
#
# References:
#   - knowledge/W2_DEBUG_ANALYSIS_2026-05-01.md (math + recommendations)
#   - knowledge/W1W2_ANALYSIS_2026-05-01.md (initial agent analysis)
#   - infra/cp2k_grotthuss_metadyn/grotthuss_metadyn.inp (v1 inp, s121, BLOCKED)
#

&GLOBAL
  PROJECT grotthuss_metadyn_v2
  RUN_TYPE MD
  PRINT_LEVEL LOW
  WALLTIME -1
  PREFERRED_DIAG_LIBRARY SCALAPACK
&END GLOBAL

&FORCE_EVAL
  METHOD Quickstep
  &DFT
    BASIS_SET_FILE_NAME BASIS_MOLOPT
    POTENTIAL_FILE_NAME GTH_POTENTIALS
    CHARGE 1                          ! same as v1: excess proton on slab+water

    ! Use v1 wfn for SCF speedup. WFN_RESTART_FILE_NAME points to the v1 wfn copy
    ! (renamed at deploy time to grotthuss_metadyn_v2-RESTART.wfn for project consistency).
    WFN_RESTART_FILE_NAME ./grotthuss_metadyn_v2-RESTART.wfn

    &QS
      EPS_DEFAULT 1.0E-12
      EXTRAPOLATION ASPC
      EXTRAPOLATION_ORDER 3
    &END QS

    &MGRID
      CUTOFF 320
      REL_CUTOFF 40
      NGRIDS 4
    &END MGRID

    &XC
      &XC_FUNCTIONAL PBE
      &END XC_FUNCTIONAL
      &VDW_POTENTIAL
        POTENTIAL_TYPE PAIR_POTENTIAL
        &PAIR_POTENTIAL
          TYPE DFTD3(BJ)
          REFERENCE_FUNCTIONAL PBE
        &END PAIR_POTENTIAL
      &END VDW_POTENTIAL
    &END XC

    &SCF
      SCF_GUESS RESTART
      MAX_SCF 500
      EPS_SCF 1.0E-5
      ADDED_MOS 100
      &DIAGONALIZATION
        ALGORITHM STANDARD
      &END DIAGONALIZATION
      &MIXING
        METHOD BROYDEN_MIXING
        ALPHA 0.2
        NBROYDEN 8
      &END MIXING
      &SMEAR
        METHOD FERMI_DIRAC
        ELECTRONIC_TEMPERATURE [K] 500.0   ! FIX (review s130): revert from 300K
                                            ! 500K = v1, ensures stable SCF for metallic Fe slab
                                            ! T_phys=300K via NVT thermostat; smearing T artificial
      &END SMEAR
      ! FIX (review s130): restore OUTER_SCF for charge convergence in metallic system
      &OUTER_SCF
        EPS_SCF 1.0E-5
        MAX_SCF 10
      &END OUTER_SCF
    &END SCF

    &POISSON
      PERIODIC XYZ
    &END POISSON
  &END DFT

  &SUBSYS
    &CELL
      A     11.022000   0.000000   0.000000
      B      0.000000  11.022000   0.000000
      C      0.000000   0.000000   6.500000
      PERIODIC XYZ
    &END CELL

    &TOPOLOGY
      ! Last frame from v1 pos-1.xyz, copied to structure_v2_restart.xyz at deploy
      COORD_FILE_NAME structure_v2_restart.xyz
      COORD_FILE_FORMAT XYZ
    &END TOPOLOGY

    &COLVAR
      &COORDINATION
        ! SAME CV as v1 (verified valid in s130 W2_DEBUG_ANALYSIS section 4):
        ! No Grotthuss exchange of H_37 observed in v1 over 11.5 ps,
        ! so CV(H_37) is faithful proxy for "specific H desorption from Fe surface".
        ATOMS_FROM 38
        ATOMS_TO   1 2 5 6 9 10 13 14 17 18 21 22 25 26 29 30 33 34
        R_0 [angstrom] 2.0
        NN 6
        ND 12
      &END COORDINATION
    &END COLVAR

    &KIND Fe
      BASIS_SET DZVP-MOLOPT-SR-GTH
      POTENTIAL GTH-PBE-q16
    &END KIND
    &KIND S
      BASIS_SET DZVP-MOLOPT-SR-GTH
      POTENTIAL GTH-PBE-q6
    &END KIND
    &KIND O
      BASIS_SET DZVP-MOLOPT-SR-GTH
      POTENTIAL GTH-PBE-q6
    &END KIND
    &KIND H
      BASIS_SET DZVP-MOLOPT-SR-GTH
      POTENTIAL GTH-PBE-q1
    &END KIND
  &END SUBSYS
&END FORCE_EVAL

&MOTION
  &MD
    ENSEMBLE NVT
    STEPS 30000                        ! 15 ps target (Q-conv via window analysis)
    TIMESTEP [fs] 0.5
    TEMPERATURE [K] 300.0
    &THERMOSTAT
      TYPE NOSE
      REGION GLOBAL
      &NOSE
        LENGTH 3
        TIMECON [fs] 500.0
        MTS 2
      &END NOSE
    &END THERMOSTAT
  &END MD

  &FREE_ENERGY
    METHOD METADYN
    &METADYN
      DO_HILLS .TRUE.
      USE_PLUMED .FALSE.
      WW [kjmol] 5.0                  ! FIX #3: 5x v1 (1.0). Single hill ≈ 2 kT.
      NT_HILLS 100                    ! same: deposit every 100 MD steps = 50 fs
      WELL_TEMPERED .TRUE.
      WTGAMMA 5                       ! FIX #2: was 10. ΔT = 4T = 1200 K, k_B ΔT = 104 meV.
      &METAVAR
        COLVAR 1
        SCALE 0.05                    ! same: σ in CV units
        ! FIX #1: upper wall moved from CV>1.2 to CV>3.0
        ! Initial CV ~ 1.4-1.7 (Fe-coord region) is now FAR from wall.
        ! Physicist review (s130): physical max ~2.6 для H в idealized hollow site,
        ! поэтому wall at 3.0 (vs 2.5 first attempt) — extra 0.4 CV margin для safety.
        ! Wall triggers only при truly unphysical hyper-coordination (>5 Fe @ d~R0).
        &WALL
          TYPE QUARTIC
          POSITION 3.0                ! changed from 1.2 (s130 fix), 2.5→3.0 (physicist review)
          &QUARTIC
            DIRECTION WALL_PLUS
            K [kjmol] 500.0
          &END QUARTIC
        &END WALL
        &WALL
          TYPE QUARTIC
          POSITION -0.1                ! same lower wall (geometric — CV≥0)
          &QUARTIC
            DIRECTION WALL_MINUS
            K [kjmol] 500.0
          &END QUARTIC
        &END WALL
      &END METAVAR
      &PRINT
        &HILLS
          &EACH
            MD 100
          &END EACH
        &END HILLS
        &COLVAR
          &EACH
            MD 10
          &END EACH
        &END COLVAR
      &END PRINT
    &END METADYN
  &END FREE_ENERGY

  &PRINT
    &TRAJECTORY
      &EACH
        MD 1
      &END EACH
      FORMAT XYZ
    &END TRAJECTORY
    &VELOCITIES
      &EACH
        MD 8                           ! Was MD 10. 4 fs/frame → Nyquist 4166 cm⁻¹
                                       ! Resolves O-H stretch ~3500 cm⁻¹ for VDOS.
                                       ! (s130 lesson from W1 vel stride bug)
      &END EACH
    &END VELOCITIES
    &RESTART
      &EACH
        MD 10
      &END EACH
      BACKUP_COPIES 2
    &END RESTART
    &RESTART_HISTORY
      &EACH
        MD 2000
      &END EACH
    &END RESTART_HISTORY
  &END PRINT
&END MOTION
